WEBVTT

00:01.120 --> 00:02.620
Dre: Forgiveness.

00:02.620 --> 00:04.250
Black people in general

00:04.250 --> 00:05.830
are very forgiving.

00:05.830 --> 00:08.790
We forgive our mayors.

00:08.790 --> 00:10.830
We forgave
a certain coffee chain

00:10.830 --> 00:14.080
for that racist manager
calling the police on us.

00:14.080 --> 00:18.330
Okay, maybe I forgave them
a little earlier than most.

00:18.330 --> 00:22.250
See, we understand
that life is hard enough.

00:22.250 --> 00:24.250
So being able
to forgive people

00:24.250 --> 00:27.210
is necessary for us
to let go and move on.

00:27.210 --> 00:30.580
[ Telephone rings,
indistinct conversations ]

00:30.580 --> 00:31.960
Yo.

00:31.960 --> 00:34.620
Perry: Hey, it's Perry --
Kyra's dad.

00:34.620 --> 00:36.080
Can I talk to her?

00:36.080 --> 00:39.210
But there's some people
you just can't forgive.

00:40.420 --> 00:42.420
[ Glass shatters ]

00:44.000 --> 00:47.170
♪♪

00:47.170 --> 00:48.880
Kyra's been with us
all these months

00:48.880 --> 00:50.960
and this is
the first time he calls?
Unbelievable.

00:50.960 --> 00:53.250
Yeah, I know, Perry. I know.
You know I know.

00:53.250 --> 00:55.210
What kind of dad would
just abandon his daughter

00:55.210 --> 00:57.580
and let her couch surf
for years?

00:57.580 --> 00:59.120
Why are we so upset?

00:59.120 --> 01:01.420
Because Kyra's
an honorary Johnson now.

01:01.420 --> 01:03.670
We accepted her with open arms.

01:03.670 --> 01:05.460
Turn off the lights
and turn off the TV

01:05.460 --> 01:07.040
because Kyra is gonna
have to take care of Kyra!

01:07.040 --> 01:09.540
Rainbow: Dre, Dre.
Hmm?

01:09.540 --> 01:11.460
Kyra's here.

01:11.460 --> 01:12.790
Hey.
Hey.

01:12.790 --> 01:15.210
Okay, maybe not.
But what choice did we have?

01:15.210 --> 01:17.790
Things were pretty rough
for her before she got to us.

01:17.790 --> 01:19.920
A couple years ago,
I stayed in a shelter for a bit,

01:19.920 --> 01:21.080
and all my stuff got stolen.

01:21.080 --> 01:22.170
Oh...
Turns out,

01:22.170 --> 01:23.620
I love to travel light.

01:23.620 --> 01:25.710
[ Laughs loudly ]

01:25.710 --> 01:27.080
Bow, I don't think
that was a joke.

01:27.080 --> 01:28.670
That one wasn't --
No.

01:28.670 --> 01:31.080
We worked hard to get her
into a better school.

01:31.080 --> 01:32.500
Well, she got in.

01:32.500 --> 01:33.250
What?
Yeah, yeah, yeah!
Oh, my goodness!

01:33.250 --> 01:34.670
I'm perfect.
[ Laughs ]

01:34.670 --> 01:37.080
She's finally comfortable
with her new life,

01:37.080 --> 01:40.330
and she's truly one of us.

01:40.330 --> 01:42.290
I think
that's a ladies' jacket.

01:42.290 --> 01:43.880
Proud of that girl.

01:43.880 --> 01:45.790
And nothing can slow her down.

01:45.790 --> 01:47.710
Except her daddy, Perry.

01:47.710 --> 01:50.170
That dude has never
had his act together.

01:50.170 --> 01:52.500
Like, he spent
all of '09

01:52.500 --> 01:55.080
squatting
in foreclosed homes.

01:55.080 --> 01:57.120
And didn't you tell me that
he was gonna try and start

01:57.120 --> 02:00.750
a vape shop/phone screen
repair store?

02:00.750 --> 02:03.380
Yes!
You talking about
Shattered Grass?

02:03.380 --> 02:04.750
I still think
that's a good idea.

02:04.750 --> 02:06.120
Mama,
what did he say?

02:06.120 --> 02:07.710
He's coming to get her.
Excuse me?

02:07.710 --> 02:09.290
Well, he just can't
take her away from us.

02:09.290 --> 02:10.710
Yeah, well,
he's coming Tuesday.

02:10.710 --> 02:12.290
Tuesday?!

02:12.290 --> 02:14.080
Oh, my God! Dre...

02:14.080 --> 02:17.500
Kyra just hit her stride
at Valley Glen.

02:17.500 --> 02:20.210
I mean, she -- she killed it
at that science fair.

02:20.210 --> 02:22.380
Yeah, she got Jack
excited about science.

02:22.380 --> 02:23.710
I know.
You -- You know
he got a C-plus

02:23.710 --> 02:26.290
on his bio test
the other day?
I know.

02:26.290 --> 02:28.120
Oh, I can't believe
Perry's doing this.

02:28.120 --> 02:29.880
Oh, I'm sorry.

02:29.880 --> 02:31.540
We don't support a black father

02:31.540 --> 02:33.500
who comes back for his child?

02:33.500 --> 02:34.880
That's who we are now?

02:34.880 --> 02:36.540
That's exactly
who we are.
Mm-hmm.

02:36.540 --> 02:38.080
And we are gonna do
whatever it takes

02:38.080 --> 02:39.290
to protect her
from this ass--

02:39.290 --> 02:42.330
Okay, don--
Oh, hey, KiKi.

02:42.330 --> 02:43.540
[ Chuckles ]
So, you --
Hey, sweetie.

02:43.540 --> 02:45.170
So, you talked
to your dad?

02:45.170 --> 02:46.830
I guess
I'm moving to Houston.

02:46.830 --> 02:50.210
Well, yeah,
that's great. Right?

02:50.210 --> 02:53.250
Honestly, I don't know
how I feel about it.

02:53.250 --> 02:56.830
It's just that things
are going pretty well here.

02:56.830 --> 02:58.620
Maybe we can figure
something out.

02:58.620 --> 03:00.580
I hope so.

03:04.210 --> 03:05.750
Okay, we need to figure
something out.

03:05.750 --> 03:08.460
Yeah, like figure out how
to plant some drugs on Perry.

03:08.460 --> 03:10.420
Mama, what you got
in your purse?

03:10.420 --> 03:12.080
Shh.

03:12.080 --> 03:13.580
You never know
who's listening.

03:13.580 --> 03:15.540
So, when are you
moving?

03:15.540 --> 03:16.960
I don't know. Soon?

03:16.960 --> 03:19.000
This sucks.
Guys, you know she's only

03:19.000 --> 03:20.330
gonna be 20 minutes
away, right?

03:20.330 --> 03:21.710
Where do you think
Houston is?

03:21.710 --> 03:23.290
In Pasadena?

03:23.290 --> 03:24.830
Th-They got
that spinach dip --

03:24.830 --> 03:26.790
You really think Kyra's dad
lives in a restaurant?

03:26.790 --> 03:28.210
No.

03:28.210 --> 03:29.670
Above a restaurant.

03:29.670 --> 03:31.330
Well, let's try
to make the most

03:31.330 --> 03:32.880
of your last days
in California.

03:32.880 --> 03:34.580
Like a bucket list.

03:34.580 --> 03:36.330
Let's go to Rodeo Drive
and tell everyone

03:36.330 --> 03:37.210
that we're Will
and Jada's kids

03:37.210 --> 03:38.460
and see all
the free stuff we get.

03:38.460 --> 03:39.830
What about chili dogs
from Larry's?

03:39.830 --> 03:40.830
I know I'm gonna
miss that.

03:40.830 --> 03:42.500
Ugh, come on.

03:42.500 --> 03:45.330
Guys, think bigger.

03:45.330 --> 03:47.620
This is L.A.

03:47.620 --> 03:49.830
We can go see
"The Brady Bunch" house

03:49.830 --> 03:53.120
or take the "Where Are They Now"
reality stars tour.

03:53.120 --> 03:55.580
Spoiler alert --
they're all working retail.

03:55.580 --> 03:56.960
Rodeo Drive it is.

03:56.960 --> 03:58.670
Junior, you make sure
there's gas in the car,

03:58.670 --> 04:00.460
and, Jack, hit the couch
in Dad's room

04:00.460 --> 04:03.420
because we're gonna need cash.
Any questions?

04:03.420 --> 04:06.750
Does Perry really think
I'm gonna let Kyra

04:06.750 --> 04:08.620
go live with
a deadbeat like him?

04:08.620 --> 04:10.790
Hey! We prefer the term

04:10.790 --> 04:12.540
"remote father."

04:12.540 --> 04:14.880
Okay, my bad.
Charlie, you're a deadbeat dad?

04:14.880 --> 04:17.290
Let he who is without bench
warrant for late child support

04:17.290 --> 04:20.000
cast the first stone.

04:20.000 --> 04:21.460
What's wrong, Dre?
Hm?

04:21.460 --> 04:23.120
Lose another one
of your sports heroes

04:23.120 --> 04:24.670
taken down
by security footage?

04:24.670 --> 04:26.620
My little cousin's
father is here

04:26.620 --> 04:28.380
to take her back
to Houston with him,

04:28.380 --> 04:29.830
and I don't want him
to take her.

04:29.830 --> 04:32.290
Ah, two Black fathers

04:32.290 --> 04:33.920
fighting to take care
of a Black youth.

04:33.920 --> 04:35.290
[ Chuckles ]

04:35.290 --> 04:37.710
It's a tale as old
as this sentence.

04:37.710 --> 04:39.250
Josh: Sometimes
I used to wish that

04:39.250 --> 04:40.920
a strong,
caring Black father

04:40.920 --> 04:42.920
would come for me
when I was a boy.

04:42.920 --> 04:44.250
Like Carl Winslow.

04:44.250 --> 04:46.250
You know,
he stood by Urkel

04:46.250 --> 04:48.290
even though he broke
everything in his house.

04:48.290 --> 04:49.960
Never disowned him.

04:49.960 --> 04:52.670
[ Voice breaking ]
And it's because he knew
family mattered...

04:52.670 --> 04:54.710
[ Cries ]
Okay, buddy.
You know what?

04:54.710 --> 04:57.120
Go take a lap.

04:57.120 --> 04:58.080
I'll be right back.

05:00.710 --> 05:02.210
[ Josh sobbing ]

05:02.210 --> 05:03.500
You know, Dre?
Hmm?

05:03.500 --> 05:04.710
Houston's all right.

05:04.710 --> 05:07.460
I mean, any city named
after Marques Houston --

05:07.460 --> 05:09.790
I mean, it can't be
all that bad, right?

05:09.790 --> 05:11.250
Mm -- Okay.

05:11.250 --> 05:14.170
Dude popping up
like this, you know,

05:14.170 --> 05:15.290
wanting to snatch her
from us?

05:15.290 --> 05:16.500
That's got
to be illegal.

05:16.500 --> 05:19.250
Dre, you are
gonna need a lawyer.

05:19.250 --> 05:20.710
Ah, okay.

05:20.710 --> 05:23.210
Criminal, civil,
marit-- Oh, gosh.

05:23.210 --> 05:25.750
How did my pool boy
get in here?

05:25.750 --> 05:27.250
Oh, you know what?
He actually -- He did.

05:27.250 --> 05:29.330
He cleaned up
a big mess for me.

05:29.330 --> 05:31.040
Time to lawyer up.

05:31.040 --> 05:32.210
I'm gonna text Bow.

05:32.210 --> 05:34.710
[ Panting ]
Guys, I am back,

05:34.710 --> 05:37.290
and I'm steady
as a rock!

05:37.290 --> 05:38.420
[ Voice breaking ]
Oh, shoot.

05:38.420 --> 05:40.330
I bet The Rock's
a great dad, too.

05:40.330 --> 05:42.000
[ Sobs ]
Stevens: For God's sakes.

05:42.000 --> 05:44.040
So we went to see one of

05:44.040 --> 05:46.330
the top family law
practitioners in the city.

05:48.080 --> 05:49.960
So...?
If the father wants her,

05:49.960 --> 05:51.830
you have absolutely
no legal recourse.

05:51.830 --> 05:53.830
What?!
You could've Googled this

05:53.830 --> 05:55.380
and saved
yourself $500.

05:57.420 --> 05:58.620
That'll be $500.

06:00.460 --> 06:02.210
So, yeah,
there's nothing we can do

06:02.210 --> 06:04.420
because we're not
her legal guardians.

06:04.420 --> 06:06.460
I told you to claim her
on your taxes,

06:06.460 --> 06:08.380
like I do
all your kids.
What?

06:08.380 --> 06:10.710
I'm technically married
to Devante.

06:10.710 --> 06:12.170
Ain't that right,
Mr. Johnson?

06:12.170 --> 06:14.790
[ Laughs ]

06:14.790 --> 06:18.170
Hey. The two of you are acting
like you've lost your minds.

06:18.170 --> 06:20.880
It's always
best for the child

06:20.880 --> 06:22.960
to be
with the parent.

06:22.960 --> 06:25.460
Is it?
Or should she be

06:25.460 --> 06:28.500
with a family who loves her
and wants her here?

06:28.500 --> 06:31.620
We all love that
little red-headed chipmunk.

06:31.620 --> 06:34.750
But her daddy's
coming Tuesday.
Hang on.

06:34.750 --> 06:37.080
What if we lock
all the doors,

06:37.080 --> 06:39.620
and when he tries
to get in,

06:39.620 --> 06:41.330
call it trespassing?

06:41.330 --> 06:43.080
Peep this, though.
Uh-huh?

06:43.080 --> 06:45.210
We leave
the doors unlocked...
Okay?

06:45.210 --> 06:46.830
...so he gets in...
Yeah.

06:46.830 --> 06:48.460
...and then it's
stand your ground.

06:48.460 --> 06:50.670
Boom!
Oh, ho,
and then we got him!

06:50.670 --> 06:52.040
Yes!
Ha, ha! Nope, nope.

06:52.040 --> 06:53.080
No, wh-- Why not?

06:53.080 --> 06:54.170
This isn't Florida.

06:54.170 --> 06:55.460
Damn it!

06:55.460 --> 06:57.500
We got to come up
with a real plan.

06:57.500 --> 06:59.210
He's gonna be here
in four days.
Yeah.

06:59.210 --> 07:00.710
[ Knock on door ]

07:00.710 --> 07:02.750
Who's that?
Perry: Is this
the Johnson residence?

07:02.750 --> 07:04.750
Wait a minute.
That sounds like Perry!

07:04.750 --> 07:05.920
He's early?

07:05.920 --> 07:08.080
What kind of
Black man is he?

07:08.080 --> 07:11.500
♪♪

07:11.500 --> 07:12.790
Surprise.

07:12.790 --> 07:15.170
Ah...
Yeah. [ Chuckles ]

07:15.170 --> 07:16.750
What are you
doing here already?

07:16.750 --> 07:18.960
We thought you weren't
coming till Tuesday.

07:18.960 --> 07:21.830
Yep. People have a tendency to
leave when they know I'm coming.

07:21.830 --> 07:23.420
Yeah.
So bam! I'm coming.

07:24.830 --> 07:26.710
Kyra!
Your daddy's here!

07:26.710 --> 07:28.290
Okay. Come on in.
Come in.

07:28.290 --> 07:30.120
This is great.
Welcome.

07:33.120 --> 07:35.540
So, Kyra's dad was here
four days early,

07:35.540 --> 07:37.120
which was smart,

07:37.120 --> 07:39.330
because we didn't have time
to plot against him.

07:39.330 --> 07:41.880
"Perry Ellis,
make 'em jealous."

07:41.880 --> 07:44.080
"Rubilene, two sugars,
one cream."

07:44.080 --> 07:46.170
You look
magnificent.

07:46.170 --> 07:47.500
Aww.

07:47.500 --> 07:49.960
Hey.
Where you been, man?

07:49.960 --> 07:51.210
What are you doing here?

07:51.210 --> 07:54.080
What he means is,
where you been, man?

07:54.080 --> 07:55.960
And what are you
doing here?
Well, I-I --

07:55.960 --> 07:58.620
I know that the two of you
feel some sort of way about me.

07:58.620 --> 07:59.960
Uh-huh.
Mm.

07:59.960 --> 08:01.960
I get it.
I've been gone a long time.

08:01.960 --> 08:03.540
But the prodigal dad
has returned.

08:03.540 --> 08:04.830
Mm.
And I returned

08:04.830 --> 08:06.540
bearing gifts
from my travels.

08:07.920 --> 08:09.500
That's right.
[ Bag rustles ]

08:09.500 --> 08:11.250
I know it gets hot in L.A.

08:11.250 --> 08:12.540
This here that
you're looking at

08:12.540 --> 08:14.670
is a custom
steering wheel cover.

08:14.670 --> 08:17.040
Oh.
Custom. One size fits all.

08:17.040 --> 08:18.790
Oh.
Put that on your steering wheel
and cover it.

08:20.080 --> 08:21.750
Hey, Dad.

08:21.750 --> 08:23.170
Hi, baby girl.

08:23.170 --> 08:24.040
Come here
and give me a hug.

08:27.380 --> 08:28.710
Kyra,

08:28.710 --> 08:31.790
your father drove all
the way here from Houston.

08:31.790 --> 08:33.120
Gonna give him
a hug?

08:33.120 --> 08:34.500
We can start
with a nod.

08:36.330 --> 08:37.750
[ Whispering ]
That seems fair, considering.
Hmph.

08:37.750 --> 08:39.460
Show me this fine house

08:39.460 --> 08:42.080
where they can keep all
the lights on during the day.

08:42.080 --> 08:43.880
I couldn't wait to get here.
As soon as I saw

08:43.880 --> 08:46.330
them pictures with you
in that red-velvet hair.

08:46.330 --> 08:49.080
I said wait till she sees
this raspberry iced tea.

08:50.750 --> 08:51.710
Oh.

08:53.330 --> 08:54.580
Bad news.

08:54.580 --> 08:56.120
Kyra's dad
is downstairs.

08:56.120 --> 08:57.380
She's leaving tonight.

08:57.380 --> 08:59.210
But I thought we were
gonna do L.A. big.

08:59.210 --> 09:01.380
Plus I even bought
these leather pants!

09:01.380 --> 09:03.880
Ooh. Man, when you miss,
you miss hard.
Oh.

09:03.880 --> 09:06.210
Look, we can still make it
to Larry's and back

09:06.210 --> 09:07.500
and get her
that chili dog.

09:07.500 --> 09:09.830
Great. I'll drive.

09:09.830 --> 09:12.170
We've got a cousin
who's about to reunite

09:12.170 --> 09:14.380
with her estranged
father.

09:14.380 --> 09:15.710
So buckle up.

09:15.710 --> 09:16.790
[ Keys jingle ]

09:16.790 --> 09:17.960
[ Whispers ]
We're running yellows.

09:17.960 --> 09:22.670
♪♪

09:22.670 --> 09:25.710
Just can't believe
how big you've gotten.

09:25.710 --> 09:28.670
I can remember when
we were the same height.

09:28.670 --> 09:30.080
How old
were you then?

09:30.080 --> 09:31.580
5.

09:31.580 --> 09:32.580
[ Whispering ]
Look at him sweet-talking her.

09:32.580 --> 09:33.790
He is not fooling me.

09:33.790 --> 09:36.920
He has unleashed
a fierce mama bear.

09:36.920 --> 09:38.540
[ Whispering ]
You know, if I could just
get him in the backyard,

09:38.540 --> 09:40.500
I could beat his ass
for trespassing.

09:40.500 --> 09:41.620
Dre.
Hmm?

09:41.620 --> 09:43.710
That's awful.

09:43.710 --> 09:45.330
We just
redid the patio.

09:45.330 --> 09:46.790
If you're gonna do that,
take him in the bathroom.

09:48.500 --> 09:49.880
Can I?

09:49.880 --> 09:51.750
I can't wait
to get back to Houston.

09:51.750 --> 09:54.000
I've been in barber college
all year.

09:54.000 --> 09:55.920
Just finally
got my license.

09:55.920 --> 09:58.120
You did?
Wow.

09:58.120 --> 10:00.620
Okay. So, you set up
in a shop already?

10:00.620 --> 10:04.420
Yeah. How much
do new barbers make?

10:04.420 --> 10:06.000
Mm, I do okay.

10:06.000 --> 10:07.620
What exactly
is "okay"?

10:07.620 --> 10:08.710
In American dollars.

10:08.710 --> 10:10.170
Hey, Kyra?

10:10.170 --> 10:12.500
Why don't you go upstairs
and get ready to go.

10:12.500 --> 10:14.380
And don't forget
those pantyhose I bought you.

10:14.380 --> 10:16.000
Okay.
And remember --

10:16.000 --> 10:17.880
roll, don't fold!

10:17.880 --> 10:20.540
Got it.
All right.

10:20.540 --> 10:22.920
And let's not forget
we're family.

10:22.920 --> 10:23.790
You're right, Mama.

10:24.830 --> 10:26.420
Hey, fam.

10:26.420 --> 10:29.000
Are you prepared
to take care of a teenager?

10:29.000 --> 10:31.080
What are you gonna do
with her schooling?

10:31.080 --> 10:33.210
Honestly, I think
she should go. You?

10:33.210 --> 10:35.920
Yes. She should
go to school, Perry.

10:35.920 --> 10:37.670
Relax. I think
there's a school

10:37.670 --> 10:39.170
right across the street
from the barber shop.

10:39.170 --> 10:41.290
You think
there's a school?

10:41.290 --> 10:44.080
Okay. How 'bout I pour
everybody some lemonade?

10:44.080 --> 10:45.250
Come on, y'all.
Sure.

10:45.250 --> 10:46.380
Dre:
I-I-I'm sure that after

10:46.380 --> 10:48.080
that long drive
Perry just did,

10:48.080 --> 10:49.540
he don't want
no lemonade.

10:49.540 --> 10:50.830
Rainbow:
Dre, what are you --

10:50.830 --> 10:52.540
I'm sure Perry
would like some water.

10:52.540 --> 10:53.330
What are --

10:54.330 --> 10:55.620
Yes.
Okay, well, come on.

10:55.620 --> 10:57.460
Let's go in the backyard
and get some water, Perry.

10:57.460 --> 10:58.830
You don't, uh,

10:58.830 --> 11:00.250
keep your water
in the refrigerator?

11:00.250 --> 11:01.960
Nope.
Faucet's broken, too.

11:01.960 --> 11:03.210
Andre.
Hmm?

11:03.210 --> 11:05.080
You're acting crazy.

11:05.080 --> 11:06.580
You need
to figure this out.

11:06.580 --> 11:08.080
Okay.

11:10.620 --> 11:12.170
I didn't...

11:12.170 --> 11:14.670
mean to upset everybody
with a beverage request.

11:14.670 --> 11:16.580
Um...

11:16.580 --> 11:18.420
what's really
going on, Dre?

11:18.420 --> 11:21.380
Look here, man. Uh...

11:21.380 --> 11:22.750
Why don't you just
do the right thing

11:22.750 --> 11:24.250
and let Kyra
stay here?

11:24.250 --> 11:27.170
She's doing
so well in school.

11:27.170 --> 11:29.920
And this is a really
important time for her.

11:29.920 --> 11:32.670
And I just -- Can't we
figure something out?

11:32.670 --> 11:35.330
Look, man, you can
cut hair here in L.A.

11:35.330 --> 11:36.710
I can make
a few phone calls.
Yes!

11:36.710 --> 11:38.420
We can help you
get an apartment.
Yes.

11:38.420 --> 11:41.000
Everything will be great.
Yes! It'll be a win-win.

11:41.000 --> 11:42.750
Guys.

11:42.750 --> 11:44.420
Thank you for
looking out for her.

11:44.420 --> 11:46.380
You did great.

11:46.380 --> 11:47.920
But I'm gonna
take it from here.

11:47.920 --> 11:50.540
[ Sighs ]
And I'm gonna do
a great job by Kyra.

11:50.540 --> 11:51.880
In Houston.

11:51.880 --> 11:53.040
And I got
a great place.

11:53.040 --> 11:55.670
I got a couch --
a great couch.

11:55.670 --> 11:58.210
Eco-friendly,
faux suede couch.

11:58.210 --> 11:59.670
What?
I don't own it all,

11:59.670 --> 12:02.830
but legally, three of five
cushions are mine.

12:02.830 --> 12:05.080
Great.

12:05.080 --> 12:07.250
I'm joking, Dre.
I got furniture.

12:07.250 --> 12:08.830
Ain't nothing funny
'bout this, Perry.

12:08.830 --> 12:10.670
Why don't you do
what you do best, man?

12:10.670 --> 12:12.040
Just leave
and turn your back on her.

12:14.120 --> 12:16.880
Okay, I'ma take
that one.

12:16.880 --> 12:18.290
And I am gonna leave.

12:20.290 --> 12:22.120
To go wait
in the car for Kyra.

12:24.920 --> 12:26.170
Okay.

12:26.170 --> 12:28.460
I, uh -- Thank you
for the, um,

12:28.460 --> 12:29.920
steering wheel cover.
Bow.

12:29.920 --> 12:31.580
But he bought it
as a gift.
Yeah. Let it go.

12:31.580 --> 12:34.040
Well, that's that.

12:34.040 --> 12:36.500
[ Door closes ]

12:36.500 --> 12:38.170
It's okay.
Okay.

12:39.750 --> 12:42.250
Jack:
[ Sighs ] Oh, no!

12:42.250 --> 12:43.460
We're not gonna
have time for this!

12:43.460 --> 12:45.170
We'll miss Kyra.

12:45.170 --> 12:46.670
What if we politely explain
our situation --

12:46.670 --> 12:48.290
Hey, guys!
They opened up

12:48.290 --> 12:49.790
another register out back.
No line!

12:49.790 --> 12:51.000
Sweet!

12:51.000 --> 12:52.540
-Let's go.
-Hurry up, hurry up!

12:52.540 --> 12:54.290
Now that all the dummies
are filtered out,

12:54.290 --> 12:56.580
it's time
to get to work.

12:56.580 --> 12:58.830
They're towing a silver Prius
around the corner!

12:58.830 --> 13:00.790
[ Rapping ]
♪ I ain't from the new school ♪

13:00.790 --> 13:02.380
♪ But I always been a leader ♪

13:02.380 --> 13:04.620
♪ J-Ro go for 24
like keefer ♪
Excuse me, sir.

13:04.620 --> 13:05.460
[ Laughs ] Hey --
[ Record scratch ]

13:08.380 --> 13:10.040
Charles.

13:10.040 --> 13:11.250
Diane.

13:11.250 --> 13:18.170
♪♪

13:18.170 --> 13:25.040
♪♪

13:25.040 --> 13:27.040
[ Knock on door ]

13:27.040 --> 13:28.960
Hey.
Hey.

13:28.960 --> 13:31.790
Kind of crazy.
I came here with one backpack,

13:31.790 --> 13:33.960
and now I have
two suitcases.

13:33.960 --> 13:36.330
Oh.
I really came up.

13:36.330 --> 13:38.420
Well...
[ Clears throat ]

13:38.420 --> 13:40.670
I actually think
we're the ones who came up.

13:40.670 --> 13:41.880
When you first got here,

13:41.880 --> 13:43.500
you wouldn't even
let me hug you.

13:43.500 --> 13:45.830
Yeah, but still...
Mm.

13:45.830 --> 13:47.380
...not feeling it.
[ Chuckles ]

13:47.380 --> 13:48.540
[ Chuckling ]
Okay.

13:48.540 --> 13:50.920
Whatever.

13:50.920 --> 13:53.830
I wish we could've convinced
your dad that you could say.

13:53.830 --> 13:56.460
I'm so sorry. I-I don't know
what else we can do.

13:56.460 --> 13:58.580
You don't
have to do anything.

13:58.580 --> 14:01.120
He drove all the way
down here from Houston.

14:01.120 --> 14:04.040
Mm-hmm.
He spent 15 months

14:04.040 --> 14:05.500
getting
a barber's license.

14:05.500 --> 14:07.960
He did.
And he dyed
his hair for me.

14:10.040 --> 14:12.170
I think he's serious
this time.

14:12.170 --> 14:14.080
We just...
[ Inhales deeply ]

14:14.080 --> 14:15.420
We want
to protect you.

14:15.420 --> 14:18.040
You don't have to.
He's my dad.

14:19.790 --> 14:21.420
Can I get
one more hug?
A small one.

14:21.420 --> 14:23.580
I wanted a big one.
S-Small one.

14:23.580 --> 14:25.080
Let's do
a medium one.
Okay.

14:25.080 --> 14:28.170
Bring it in.
[ Chuckles ]

14:28.170 --> 14:30.580
All right,
sweetheart.

14:30.580 --> 14:33.120
You finish
packing up.

14:33.120 --> 14:34.500
Hey.

14:34.500 --> 14:36.670
Please take that history book
right there.

14:36.670 --> 14:38.330
Texas has, uh...

14:39.830 --> 14:42.080
...a weird version
of the Civil War.

14:42.080 --> 14:44.580
♪♪

14:44.580 --> 14:45.920
Rainbow: Dre.
Hmm?

14:45.920 --> 14:49.000
If it makes you
feel any better,

14:49.000 --> 14:50.540
she actually
wants to go with him.

14:50.540 --> 14:51.580
[ Scoffs ]

14:51.580 --> 14:53.120
She's 15.
I know.

14:53.120 --> 14:54.880
She doesn't know
what she wants.

14:54.880 --> 14:56.120
Yesterday...
Mm-hmm?

14:56.120 --> 14:58.000
...she wanted
a tattoo on her lip

14:58.000 --> 14:59.710
that said "Elbow."
What?

14:59.710 --> 15:02.380
Yeah. She said
it was ironic.

15:02.380 --> 15:04.790
That's not ironic!
Yeah, it's moronic.

15:04.790 --> 15:06.210
Okay, but, Dre,

15:06.210 --> 15:09.170
I feel like
we need to get on board.

15:09.170 --> 15:10.460
Or what kind
of relationship

15:10.460 --> 15:12.000
are we gonna have with her
in the long run?

15:12.000 --> 15:13.170
You're right, babe.

15:15.170 --> 15:17.710
It's gonna
be hard, but...

15:17.710 --> 15:19.170
you're right.

15:19.170 --> 15:20.960
Think maybe we should
spend a little time with her

15:20.960 --> 15:22.500
before she leaves?

15:22.500 --> 15:24.500
That is a good idea.

15:24.500 --> 15:26.040
All right.
I'll be right up.
Okay.

15:27.380 --> 15:33.790
♪♪

15:33.790 --> 15:40.290
♪♪

15:43.620 --> 15:44.830
What the hell's
going on, man?

15:44.830 --> 15:46.250
Oh, hey, Dre.

15:46.250 --> 15:48.880
I, uh, didn't want
to bug you for a jump,

15:48.880 --> 15:50.880
so I just decided
to do it myself.

15:50.880 --> 15:54.040
You gonna help a brother out,
or you just gonna stand there?

15:54.040 --> 15:55.420
Let me ask you
something, man.

15:58.170 --> 15:59.830
Why do you want
to blow up Kyra's life?

16:03.500 --> 16:05.540
Look, Dre,
I know my life may look

16:05.540 --> 16:08.290
a little different than yours
because you come up

16:08.290 --> 16:10.120
and you're really doing
your thing now.

16:11.670 --> 16:12.790
But I got it
from here.

16:12.790 --> 16:14.830
That's just it, Perry.
You don't.

16:14.830 --> 16:16.460
You never have.

16:16.460 --> 16:19.120
And now you want to roll
the dice with Kyra's future

16:19.120 --> 16:21.380
because you worry that
she's old enough to figure out

16:21.380 --> 16:23.460
what kind of man
you really are.

16:23.460 --> 16:26.790
How do you know that
Kyra staying with relatives

16:26.790 --> 16:29.540
wasn't the best move
at the time?

16:29.540 --> 16:31.000
How do you know that
her coming with me

16:31.000 --> 16:32.710
isn't the best move now?

16:35.330 --> 16:36.460
Maybe you're right.

16:38.790 --> 16:40.960
Maybe I just don't
get you because...

16:42.540 --> 16:44.170
...I never abandoned
my kids.

16:45.580 --> 16:47.830
Andre!

16:47.830 --> 16:49.540
Get in here.

16:49.540 --> 16:51.620
[ Quietly ]
Your mama's calling.

16:51.620 --> 16:54.460
♪♪

16:57.920 --> 16:59.710
[ Door slams ]

16:59.710 --> 17:01.080
Sit down.

17:01.080 --> 17:03.290
♪♪

17:03.290 --> 17:04.290
[ Chair scrapes ]

17:04.290 --> 17:05.710
What do you think
you're doing?

17:05.710 --> 17:07.460
Fighting for someone

17:07.460 --> 17:09.170
who doesn't have
anyone to fight for her.

17:09.170 --> 17:10.750
Bow's out, you're out.

17:10.750 --> 17:12.330
Nobody's out,

17:12.330 --> 17:14.080
we're just trying to do
what's best for the girl!

17:14.080 --> 17:16.380
What's best for the girl
is stability, Mama!

17:17.500 --> 17:18.710
I know what it's like

17:18.710 --> 17:20.750
to deal with a father
who isn't always there.

17:20.750 --> 17:24.080
Yeah, but you still
wanted to be with him.

17:25.500 --> 17:28.830
And when he walked back in,
I wanted to put

17:28.830 --> 17:30.960
my hand
in some lemonade, too!

17:33.040 --> 17:35.120
But he was
trying to do better,

17:35.120 --> 17:37.500
the same way
this man is.

17:37.500 --> 17:39.620
Hold up, Mama, are you asking me
to forgive Perry?

17:39.620 --> 17:41.000
Because I can't do that.

17:41.000 --> 17:43.250
No, I'm asking you
to get out of the way

17:43.250 --> 17:45.790
as the man tries
to redeem himself.

17:45.790 --> 17:47.670
I did that for you

17:47.670 --> 17:50.620
so you could build
a relationship with your father.

17:52.080 --> 17:55.000
Don't you think Kyra
deserves the same chance?

18:00.000 --> 18:01.500
It's just
so hard to do.

18:01.500 --> 18:02.880
It is hard.

18:05.290 --> 18:07.500
But, hey,
it worked for me.

18:07.500 --> 18:09.380
Your daddy lives here,

18:09.380 --> 18:12.540
so I get to put toenails
in his bedsheets.

18:12.540 --> 18:13.790
[ Chuckles ]

18:16.210 --> 18:17.500
Junior:
Guys, Grandma texted.

18:17.500 --> 18:18.790
Kyra's about to leave.

18:18.790 --> 18:21.120
[ Sighs ]
What are we going to do?

18:21.120 --> 18:22.500
There's four people
ahead of us.

18:22.500 --> 18:24.380
Counter person:
Greg! Order for Greg!

18:24.380 --> 18:30.710
♪♪

18:30.710 --> 18:32.540
[ Diane clears throat ]

18:32.540 --> 18:37.290
♪♪

18:37.290 --> 18:38.580
Ooh.

18:39.790 --> 18:41.420
Oh, wow.

18:41.420 --> 18:43.170
You must
be Greg, too.

18:43.170 --> 18:44.460
You know, we -- we have
a dad that's named --

18:44.460 --> 18:45.920
Run!

18:45.920 --> 18:47.290
Hey! That's my food!

18:49.250 --> 18:51.120
All right, sweetie.

18:51.120 --> 18:52.830
Now, you know
your hair's not gonna

18:52.830 --> 18:54.670
lie down like that
in Houston, right?

18:54.670 --> 18:56.710
I got you
some edge control,

18:56.710 --> 18:59.500
ponytail holders,
and a wave cap.

18:59.500 --> 19:02.040
Humidity does not
discriminate.

19:02.040 --> 19:03.750
[ Laughs ]
I love you.

19:03.750 --> 19:05.210
Thank you.
Yeah.

19:05.210 --> 19:07.120
I know your dad wants
to get on the road,

19:07.120 --> 19:09.380
but I so wish
that the kids were here

19:09.380 --> 19:11.040
so they could
say goodbye to you.

19:11.040 --> 19:12.580
I'm really
gonna miss you guys.

19:12.580 --> 19:15.170
Oh, we're gonna miss you.
I love you, sweetheart.

19:15.170 --> 19:17.830
Oh, you know, Houston
is only three hours away,

19:17.830 --> 19:19.420
and I'm always happy

19:19.420 --> 19:21.250
to get away
from these guys.

19:21.250 --> 19:23.460
[ Dre chuckles ]

19:23.460 --> 19:25.750
[ Whispering ] Hey, look here,
baby girl. Uh...

19:25.750 --> 19:27.330
here's $500.

19:27.330 --> 19:29.120
And, uh,

19:29.120 --> 19:30.710
my mama's Life Alert.

19:30.710 --> 19:32.540
If anything jumps off,
you just push that button.

19:32.540 --> 19:34.620
But --
Hey, shh.
Come on. All right?

19:34.620 --> 19:36.210
[ Louder ] Our door is open
for you anytime, okay?

19:36.210 --> 19:37.920
Thank you.
Okay.

19:37.920 --> 19:39.170
Hey, um...

19:40.420 --> 19:41.710
Perry.

19:43.540 --> 19:45.040
Look, man.

19:45.040 --> 19:47.580
I don't mess with you, and
I'm never gonna mess with you.

19:47.580 --> 19:48.750
But I'm not gonna
stand in your way

19:48.750 --> 19:52.080
because baby girl,

19:52.080 --> 19:53.540
she needs you.

19:55.120 --> 19:57.290
But if you blow it
this time,

19:57.290 --> 19:59.830
we gonna get
that drink of water.

19:59.830 --> 20:01.580
That's a drink of water
we'll never have.

20:04.750 --> 20:06.670
Be safe on the road, man.
You got precious cargo.

20:08.040 --> 20:09.290
Excellent.

20:09.290 --> 20:11.250
Perry: Now, how do I
get to the I-10?

20:11.250 --> 20:13.080
All right. Back up.
Well, you got
to go down to Ventura --

20:13.080 --> 20:14.330
Turn to the left and turn to --
No, I know. Get on the --

20:14.330 --> 20:15.750
Okay. I-I got it.

20:15.750 --> 20:17.380
[ Ruby chuckles ]

20:17.380 --> 20:18.620
[ Car door closes ]

20:18.620 --> 20:20.210
[ Engine starts ]

20:20.210 --> 20:22.580
Ugh, I hope
this works out.

20:22.580 --> 20:24.460
I know how much
they both want it.

20:24.460 --> 20:26.460
Yeah.
Hey, baby.
[ Vehicle departing ]

20:26.460 --> 20:27.960
Did he go upstairs?

20:27.960 --> 20:29.420
Don't think so.

20:29.420 --> 20:30.250
I didn't
check his pockets.

20:33.750 --> 20:37.040
♪ Get your back
up off the wall ♪
♪ 'Cause I heard
all the people sayin' ♪

20:37.040 --> 20:38.750
♪ Get down on it ♪
♪ Come on and ♪

20:38.750 --> 20:40.790
♪ Get down on it ♪
♪ If you really want it ♪

20:40.790 --> 20:42.920
♪ Get down on it ♪
♪ You've got to feel it ♪

20:42.920 --> 20:44.880
♪ Get down on it ♪
♪ Get down on it ♪

20:44.880 --> 20:47.120
Who are these fools?
They're my cousins.

20:47.120 --> 20:48.670
They talk
about my parenting

20:48.670 --> 20:50.710
and they got kids that
run up on armed adults?

20:50.710 --> 20:53.380
Did someone order
a Larry's chili dog?

20:53.380 --> 20:55.210
This is so nice.

20:55.210 --> 20:58.580
And you got enough
for Uncle Pernard, too?

20:58.580 --> 21:00.250
We, uh --
We did, yep.

21:00.250 --> 21:02.210
We got you
this whole big bag.

21:02.210 --> 21:03.500
Yep.

21:04.790 --> 21:06.000
Diane:
We're gonna miss you.

21:06.000 --> 21:07.500
It's been great
having you with us.

21:07.500 --> 21:08.920
Good luck
in Houston.

21:08.920 --> 21:11.080
You guys
are the best.

21:11.080 --> 21:12.670
Yeah. Good looking out,
Greg!

21:12.670 --> 21:14.120
[ Bag rustles ]

21:14.120 --> 21:17.250
♪ You gotta
get on the groove ♪

21:17.250 --> 21:19.080
[ Sighs ] Wow.

21:19.080 --> 21:20.080
Uncle Pernard
seems nice.
